news.title: The September jobs report is finally coming out Thursday. Here's what it is expected to show
news.summary: The jobs report is due at 8:30 a.m. ET. It is forecast to show a gain of 50,000 jobs in the public and private sectors.

news.title: Walmart hikes sales and earnings forecast as it attracts shoppers across incomes
news.summary: Walmart may offer the clearest snapshot of U.S. consumer health so far this retail earnings season. Walmart caters to shoppers across incomes.

news.title: Nvidia stock pops 5% in premarket trading after stronger-than-expected results
news.summary: The AI chipmaker's strong quarterly earnings have boosted global AI stocks. The chipmaker is one of the biggest names in the field of artificial intelligence.

news.title: Ukraine under pressure amid reports Russia and U.S. have devised a secret peace plan
news.summary: Senior U.S. military officials are in Ukraine on Thursday. Reports emerged that Washington and Moscow had devised a secret 28-point peace plan.

news.title: Self-storage real estate has ‘close to zero’ correlation to the broader economy. That's a good thing
news.summary: Over the last 15 years, self-storage has outperformed industrial, multifamily, office and retail in net operating income, a new Heitman report says.

news.title: This sleeper AI risk for stocks in 2026 has got Wall Street talking over the past few weeks
news.summary: A slowdown in corporate buybacks as AI players add debt could steal an important source of demand from the market. The market is expected to grow at around 10 per cent this year.

news.title: Why Verizon’s new CEO is cutting 13,000 jobs at the wireless company
news.summary: CEO Dan Schulman says layoffs will make Verizon “faster and more focused.” Verizon’s stock has been a major laggard and the company has failed to show annual earnings growth.

news.title: The war’s not over: JPMorgan says investors were too quick to sell Europe defense stocks on hopes of Ukraine peace
news.summary: The war in Ukraine has catalyzed a dramatic rerating of defense stocks in Europe. Defense stocks are up more than 10 per cent since the start of the year.

news.title: Walmart’s stock falls as disappointing Sam’s Club sales mar an otherwise upbeat report
news.summary: Sales at Sam’s Club stores open more than a year rose less than Wall Street had expected. When rival Costco last reported, the average person was spending less than ayear earlier.

news.title: Small stocks haven’t beaten large caps in more than two decades — but they’re trying
news.summary: Odds are against small caps after long stretches where they’ve lagged behind. Odds of a small team making it to the World Cup are slim to none.
